 to bypass\"\n                              - code [ref=e370]: requireMention\n                              - text: gating. The feature is cleanly implemented as an opt-in, backward-compatible flag.\n                            - paragraph [ref=e371]:\n                              - strong [ref=e372]: \"Key changes:\"\n                            - list [ref=e373]:\n                              - listitem [ref=e374]:\n                                - text: New\n                                - code [ref=e375]: requireExplicitMention\n                                - text: field added to\n                                - code [ref=e376]: SlackThreadConfig\n                                - text: type and\n                                - code [ref=e377]: SlackThreadSchema\n                                - text: Zod schema\n                              - listitem [ref=e378]:\n                                - text: Value flows from provider config →\n                                - code [ref=e379]: SlackMonitorContext\n                                - text: →\n                                - code [ref=e380]: prepare.ts\n                                - text: where it gates\n                                - code [ref=e381]: implicitMention\n                                - text: computation\n                              - listitem [ref=e382]:\n                                - code [ref=e383]: implicitMention\n                                - text: is now\n                                - code [ref=e384]: \"false\"\n                                - text: whenever\n                                - code [ref=e385]: \"threadRequireExplicitMention: true\"\n                                - text: \", leaving only\"\n                                - code [ref=e386]: wasMentioned\n                                - text: (explicit\n                                - code [ref=e387]: \"@bot\"\n                                - text: or mention-regex matches) to satisfy the mention gate\n                              - listitem [ref=e388]: 3 new tests cover enabled, disabled, and explicit-mention scenarios; all test helper defaults updated\n                              - listitem [ref=e389]: Documentation and UI hints added\n                            - paragraph [ref=e390]:\n                              - strong [ref=e391]: \"Observations (non-blocking):\"\n                            - list [ref=e392]:\n                              - listitem [ref=e393]:\n                                - text: The option only takes effect when\n                                - code [ref=e394]: \"requireMention: true\"\n                                - text: is also active; setting\n                                - code [ref=e395]: \"requireExplicitMention: true\"\n                                - text: alone with\n                                - code [ref=e396]: \"requireMention: false\"\n                                - text: is a silent no-op.\n                              - listitem [ref=e397]:\n                                - text: The new option is global-only, whereas\n                                - code [ref=e398]: requireMention\n                                - text: supports per-channel overrides.\n                              - listitem [ref=e399]:\n                                - text: Mention-regex patterns (\n                                - code [ref=e400]: mentionPatterns\n                                - text: ) still satisfy\n                                - code [ref=e401]: wasMentioned\n                                - text: even with\n                                - code [ref=e402]: \"requireExplicitMention: true\"\n                                - text: \", consistent with the broader mention system design.\"\n                            - 'heading \"Confidence Score: 5/5\" [level=3] [ref=e403]'\n                            - paragraph [ref=e404]: This PR is safe to merge — the change is strictly additive, defaults to existing behavior (false), and is correctly integrated across all layers.\n                            - paragraph [ref=e405]: \"No P0 or P1 issues found. All remaining observations are minor design-limitation notes (no per-channel support, no explicit docs note about requiring requireMention: true). The implementation is correct, backward-compatible, and well-tested.\"\n                            - paragraph [ref=e406]: No files require special attention.\n                            - group [ref=e407]:\n                              - generic \"Important Files Changed\" [ref=e408] [cursor=pointer]:\n                                - heading \"Important Files Changed\" [level=3] [ref=e409]\n                            - paragraph [ref=e410]:\n                              - subscript [ref=e411]:\n                                - text: \"Reviews (1): Last reviewed commit:\"\n                                - 'link \"\\\"feat(slack): add thread.requireExplicitM...\\\"\" [ref=e412] [cursor=pointer]':\n                                  - /url: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/commit/1ecdb19844e5cde5312461dcf3171c75e83d26aa\n                                - text: \"|\"\n                                - link \"Re-trigger Greptile\" [ref=e413] [cursor=pointer]:\n                                  - /url: https://app.greptile.com/api/retrigger?id=26882407\n                - generic [ref=e415]:\n                  - link \"@safonovklim\" [ref=e417] [cursor=pointer]:\n                    - /url: /safonovklim\n                    - img \"@safonovklim\" [ref=e418]\n                  - generic [ref=e420]:\n                    - generic [ref=e421]:\n                      - group [ref=e424]:\n                        - button \"Show options\" [ref=e425] [cursor=pointer]:\n                          - img \"Show options\" [ref=e428]\n                      - heading \"safonovklim commented Mar 31, 2026last week\" [level=3] [ref=e430]:\n    